    "body": "### Problem\n\nSome language servers (like [Powershell Editor Services](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShellEditorServices#named-pipesunix-domain-sockets-recommended)) support connecting to them via named pipes (on Windows) or unix domain sockets (on Unix). Currently, the Neovim LSP client does not support this type of connection for LSPs (it supports using stdio and tcp).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe Neovim LSP client would be able to connect to an LSP via named pipes / unix domain sockets.",
